      <p><font color="#8080C0" face="Bookman Old Style"><small>The MUDs I played saved your
      corpse pfile to disk, and thus it was still there after a crash/reboot. I guess it depends
      upon which MUD you're playing. </small></font></p>
      <p><font color="#8080C0" face="Bookman Old Style"><small>And in case you haven't guessed,
      corpse files are saved to disk in EverQuest :)</small></font></p>
    </blockquote>
    <p align="left"><font face="Arial" color="#C1C1FF"><strong><a name="BG lovin...">BG
    lovin...</a> </strong></font><a href="mailto:rbowmaster@shaw.wave.ca"><small>- Bowmeister</small></a><br>
    <small>As always the Baldur's Gate message boards are THE place to be be if you wanna find
    out the movement rate for that <font color="#FFFFFF"><strong>one legged halfling of love</strong></font>
    you rolled up. There's a bunch of new info bits floating around, starting with some short
    and sweet answers from Dr. Ray...</small></p>
    <blockquote>
      <p align="left"><font color="#8080C0" face="Bookman Old Style"><small><i>1. Do the Fighter
      classes get the ability to make two weapons swings per round after 7th level in BG?</i><br>
      <b>7th level fighters and above get 1.5 attacks per round base (independent of
      specialization, ranged weapons multipliers).</b><br>
      <br>
      <i>2. Are the cleric and druid spells seperated into there respected spheres? IE Druids
      get weather spells and Clerics get higher level Devination spells. But each dont get
      spells not in there Spheres of influence?</i><br>
      <b>No.</b><br>
      <br>
      <i>3. Do you accept bribes for getting ppl into the limited beta going on down in
      Calafornia =-)</i><br>
      <b>No. I wish!</b></small></font></p>
    </blockquote>
    <p><small>And a bit from Mark Brockington on BG Display modes...</p>
    </small><blockquote>
      <p align="left"><small><font color="#8080C0" face="Bookman Old Style">BG uses
      EnumDisplayModes to determine which colour depths are available. Some 2MB cards don't have
      24-bit, while others don't have 32-bit support in their drivers. These bit-depths are
      grayed out on the options page if they are not available.</font></small></p>
    </blockquote>
    <p><small>And finally a bit from Dr. Ray again, this time looking at just why they are
    having a public beta when the game should be out right away...</p>
    </small><blockquote>
      <p align="left"><font color="#8080C0" face="Bookman Old Style"><small>We are quite close,
      so don't worry. It's just that we want to get a fresh view of the game - from the consumer
      perspective - of the almost-completed product, BEFORE we put it in a box, so that we can
      try and correct any remaining problems that we can't see anymore. We are being obsessive
      about trying to find the bugs in the game, and this limited beta test (more like a focus
      group really, except that we're also getting bugs from them), in trying to intensively
      identify any major things that have been overlooked because we've gotten too close to the
      game in the past few months of bug fixing and testing. Plus to test the hell out of the
      completed multiplayer code to make sure that we don't have any unhappy people because they
      can't connect...<br>
      <br>
      I don't anticipate that this additional testing will in any way delay the release of the
      product - it will be concurrent with the last week or two of testing. It's a great idea
      and we look forward to hearing the testers' frank comments, all in the name of improving
      the game.</small></font></p>
    </blockquote>
    <p align="left"><font face="Arial" color="#C1C1FF"><strong><a name="F2 Patch update">F2
    Patch update</a> </strong></font><a href="mailto:rbowmaster@shaw.wave.ca"><small>-
    Bowmeister</small></a><br>
    <small>The man Feargus posted another update on the official Fallout2 page last
    night...since I <font color="#FFFFFF"><strong>hate to be the bearer of bad news</strong></font>,
    I'll just repost it and he can feel bad :)...</small></p>
    <blockquote>
      <p align="left"><font color="#8080C0" face="Bookman Old Style"><small>We found two more
      problems with the car late yesterday afternoon that needed to be fixed. So we had to build
      another version of the patch. </p>
      <p>QA is testing the patch right now. Some people here at Interplay/BIS want it released
      as soon as possible, others want to check it as thoroughly as possible. I am leaning
      towards checking it as thouroughly as possible, because I don't want to release a buggy
      patch. </p>
      <p>We are really, really trying to get it out by tomorrow night, so everyone can play over
      the weekend. However, if we find some serious bugs tomorrow then it might not happen. We
      are working on it, and I am as frustrated as everyone else that things keep on coming up
      that need to be fixed. </p>
      <p>Also, in order for me to help get it done I am not going to be able to be at my desk
      that much. This means that I will not be responding to e-mail that quickly over the next
      couple of days. </p>
      <p>Thanks, <br>
      -Feargus (<a href="mailto:furquhart@interplay.com">furquhart@interplay.com</a>) </small></font></p>
    </blockquote>
    <p align="left"><font face="Arial" color="#C1C1FF"><strong><a name="Mornin'...">Mornin'...</a>
    </strong></font><a href="mailto:rbowmaster@shaw.wave.ca"><small>- Bowmeister</small></a><br>
    <small>Another day, another archive... Come on Brad, Our <font color="#FFFFFF"><strong>lives
    are starting to flash before our eyes</strong></font> here (Well, I'm assuming it's my
    life - there's a couple of years I was only semi conscious for). Well, hopfully Half Life
    will start showing up in Canada today...probably not till Monday though. Can't wait to
    rant and rave along with everyone else on this one :)</small></td>
